<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- D major with Bm secondary key area. G#/^G in bar 6 is melody-only (Mixolydian/Aeolian flavor).
- Bars 1-2: Root-pos D and A in LH, RH light thirds/sixths above. Bm (vi) provides emotional depth.
- Bars 3-4: G-A7 bass motion supports descending melody B-A-G-F. Half cadence on A.
- Bars 5-8: Return arc D→Bm→A pattern; quartal voicing on A for open sound (bar 8).
- Bar 9: G→C#° sequential motion. C#° voicing C3-E3-G3-B3 (fully diminished color).
- Bars 11-12: Climax ascending lines in both RH and bass leading to high D5 on downbeat of 12.
- Bars 13-14: Final D-A-D cadence, suspension in RH bar 13.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bar 11 RH walking scale G4-A4-B4-C#5 contrary to static LH chord changes below
- Bar 12 RH climax reaches G5 as melody climbs to E5 — both at peaks simultaneously
- Bar 3 RH ascends D5-E5-F#5-A4 as melody descends B4-A4-G4-F#4 (contrary motion)

TEXTURE ARC:
- Single note pickup → light 2-voice RH (bars 1-5) → 7th chord color (bars 6-8) → climax bars 11-12 → final settling resolution
